{"/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_goyle_ver01/data/sn82007637/00516993832/1958061301/0301.xml":{"full_text":"4 How To Buys\nSome Sellers Hoax Public\nWith Recession Bargains'\nBy SIDNEY MARGOLIUS\nBetter watch the.quality of the things you buy espe\ncially carefully during this recession. Some manufacturers\nand food packers are reducing quality and playing other\ntricks to make their prices seem lower than they actually\nare.\nFor example, a manufac\nturer of casing for frank\nfurters, reports some meat proc\nessors are making frankfurters\nthinner but the same length so\nhere are as many as twelve in\na pound instead of the usual\neight or ten.\nThe manufacturers are doing\nthis, the casing company ex\nplains, because housewives are\nseeking more for their money in\nthis recession.. You aren\u2019t of\ncourse, getting any more for\nyour money this way.\nIt's also necessary to keep a\nsharp eye on the quality of pro\nduce. The U. S. Agricultural\nMarketing Service reports con\ncern over misrepresentation' of\nquality by some growers and\nshippers. Unlike most other\nfoods, fresh fruits and vegetables\nmay be labeled with the U. S.\ngrades without actual official in\nspection. The authorities depend\non occasional sample checks at\nthe markets to catch up with dis\nhonest sellers.\nIN THESE DAYS when many\nfresh-product items as potatoes\nare already packaged, it\u2019s dif\nficult to eheck quality before\nyou buy. Thus, safest buys are\nthose packaged fruits and vege\ntables which not only say on the\ncontainer \"U. S. Grade No. 1\u201d\nor \u201cU. S. Grade A\u201d, its the case\nmay be, but also are labeled:\n\u201cPacked under continuous in\nspection of the U. S. Dept, of\nAgriculture.\u201d\nAlso watch the quality of\nclothing at this time. A business\nnewspaper reports some manu\nfacturers are holding down costs\nby using more machine stitch\ning, reducing the number of but\ntons and amount of trimmings.\nElimination of mere decoration\nwon\u2019t affect wearability. In fact,\nimple dresses are more versa\n\u2018dile. But it\u2019s extra important\nnow to examine the basic qual\nity of seams, hems, plackets, but\ntons and buttonholes.\nJuly is a month of important\nclearances, and a good time to\nshop for summer dresses; men\u2019s\nsummer suits, slacks and shirts;\nshoes; refrigerators; washing\nmachines; television sets, and\nused cars. Note also that oil\ntanks and coal bins can be filled\nat savings of five to ten per cent\nbefore the autumn rush.\nONE PECULIAR DEVELOP\nMENT in thia recession is \u201ccon\ncealed price cuts\u201d. Manufactur\ners have been reluctant to open\nly reduce prices but instead are\noffering retailers many special\nshort-term merchandising allow\nances. They make these tempo\nrary reductions in the hope the\nrecession will end before they\nare forced to cut prices openly.\nFor example, a leading manu\nfacturer of power tools cuts\nprices on two or three models\nas much as 30 per cent for just\none month. Several TV manu\nfacturers have special-priced\nconsole and portable TV sets $62\nto $110 below previous listings.\nAuto manufacturers resist cut\nting list prices but do give deal\ners special merchandising al\nlowances of $100 on a car so\nthey can cut prices late in the\nmodel season.\nBut you have to do extra com\nparison-shopping. Not all mod\nels are reduced even in the same\nmanufacturer's line. For exam\nple, you\u2019ll find a leading tool\nmanufacturer has slashed the\nprice of his quarter-inch drill\nkit, so the complete kit costs no\nmore than the drill alone.\nBECKMAN OPTICAL CO.\nEstablished 1874\nOldest Optical Company\nla Toledo\nMINEE, OPTOMETRIST\nPhone CH. 3-5512\n203 Edward Lamb Bldg.\nGray-Price Wedding Set For\nSaturday at Glenwood Church\nPastor Roy C. Hoch will officiate at the wedding tomor\nrow of Mary Jane Gray and James Price in Glenwood Luth\neran Church.\nMr. Price, an employee of the New York Central, is the\nson of Mrs. Virginia Pattross. His stepfather, Elmer Pat\ntross is employed at Willys.\nMiss Gray is the daughter of\nGeorge Gray who works in Dept\nE of Champion. She is a grad\nuate of Scott High School and is\nreceptionist in the office of Dr.\nChilmonczyk.\nFor her wedding the bride\nhas chosen a full length\nwhite embroidered chantilly\nlace gown with tiny sleeves and\naccented in back with five tiers\nof lace, and a fingertip veil. Her\nattendants, Margie Coveney,\nmaid of honor, and bridesmaids\nJudy Gray, Arlene Doremus and\nPat Boulis will wear princess\nstyle ice-blue cotton silk baller\nina dresses with embroidered\ngores and tiny sleeves.\nMr. Price\u2019s best man will be\nhis brother Chet Price and Joe\nCoveney. Eugene Zmijewski and!\nBill Murrin will serve as ushers.!\nA reception wifi be held at the\nWalter Weller Post following\nthe ceremony. After a honey\nFather Knows Best:\nCrossing A Picket Line Is\nLike Stabbing A Union Man\nTUNIOR AND Sis Toledo had a problem. Father\u2019s Day.\n\u201cLook, brother, our dad\u2019s the greatest and I th\nwe ought to do something for him,\u201d started Sis.\n\u201cWell,\u201d Junior remarked, somewhat hesitantly, \u201cI hear\non the radio and television that Lasalles\u2019 has a contest going\nand I think\non\n99\n\u201cYou know darn well\nthat\u2019s out,\u201d retorted Sis. \u201cDad\nwould tan us good!\u201d\n\u201cYeah,\u201d sighed Junior, \u201cand\nI guess we\u2019d deserve it.\u201d\n\u201cStill, Sister sort of thought\nout loud, \u201cthat strike at Lasal\nles\u2019 has been going on an awful\nlong time. They don\u2019t seem to\nbe getting anywhere and I see\na number of people going into\nthe store. Maybe it wouldn\u2019t be\nso bad to just enter the con\nALonie2\n1\nRe-.\nIIE=\n7\ni\nl\nII\nV\nGasiotouki JbmMat\nRonald C Cook Director\nCompletely Air Conditioned\n1\nUT.\n4\n1\nIM\n4\nI\nToledo's Modern Funeral Home\nPhone CH 4-9581\n3302 Lagrange St.\nSpacious Visitors\u2019 Parking Lot\nft\n1I1 M\nI!\nIII\n8\n000000000tep0ness0sese,\n\n(11\n?TP9\nThe Search is on\nMiss Union\n-for\nSecretary of 1958\n10/81AS\nf\n.Hi\nrora\nM:\n1\nr\n$300 in U. S. Savings Bond* and a\nREMINGTON QUIET-RITER Portable\nTypewriter.\nGREAT\nPRIZES\nFIRST PRIZE\nA check for $1,000 and a wook\u2019s\nall-expenses-paid vacation. A\nREMINGTON QuIT-RITER\u00ae Port\nable Typewriter.\nTHIRD PR\nM:\nA $200 U. Saving* Bond and a I\nREMINGTON QUIET-RITER Portable I\nTypewriter. a\n20 Honorable Mention Awards\nA $25 U. S. Savings Bond. I\nembaetnsat\nr&^^s+wv^s***.*****\narsmeubbosnned\n099990000.4N*\nA%P? 54/45090820%\nSecretaries Stenographers Bookkeepers\nRecords Clerks., every female employee of a\nlabor union in the U.S.A, is eligible to win this\ncontest\u2014provided only that you will have\nworked in your present organization for one\nyear by August 1, 1958.\nOfficial entry blanks, together with complete\ncontest rules,'are now being distributed to\nunions throughout the country. Additional\nforms can be obtained by writing to \u201cMiss\nUnion Secretary Contest,\" c/o Union Adver\ntising Service, 302 Fifth Ave, New York 1, N.Y\nDeadline for entries is September 15th\u2014but\nPHI WMIIIIUUI u M JI. JJhU j J 0 II ill WUPODM/I So-ooAXN0P0T/EME0IUWP6\ndon\u2019t wait for deadline day...get your entry\nform and complete your entry right now.\n\nMro. Kothloon Kinniek of Borkoloy,\nCalif..winnar of tho Miu Union See\nrotary of 1957 Contoot, will bo otto\nof tho jui^oo of thio 1958 Contoot.\nThe \"Mb* Union Secrelary\u201d Contort is spensored by\nBGensirgtore BGezren\nDvsION OF SPEEHY (ANO CRPORATON\n&MAINOTON RAND office equipment proudly enrries the vales label at the LAM.\n\u2022mi the IB.EW.,\nAPLCIO.\nscnt\nMARY JANE GRAY\nmoon trip through the south, the\ncouple will live at 3034 Park\nwood Avenue.\n\"Awei, it seems to me that if\nit was wrong to cross the picket\n41. grics Hav nr the first\nIV wao *\u20186Y**S 11)7- era\nline the first day or the first\nweek, it would be even worse\nto cross it in the seventh month,\noffered Junior, \u201cbut maybe we\nought to talk to Mom about it.\nWHEN THEY found Mom\nweeding her small flower gar*\nden in the back yard, they ex\nplained the problem to her and\n_ 22.1 2 A **sa1a\nU1sssts \u2022-/Y711111\u2014\nasked, \u201cDo you think it would\nbe all right for us to enter the\ncontest?\u201d\nMother weighed the problem\nfor a few minutes. She thought\nabout the lady down the block\nwho showed her a dress she d\npurchased at the store last week.\nShe recalled the store\u2019s ad in\nthe Sunday paper. There were\n_ couple of items mentioned they\ncould use. Maybe\n\u201cI\u2019m not sure, children, she\ntold them. \u201cBut, I think I\u2019d\nbetter talk it over with Dad\na\nfirst.\u201d _\nDad darn near blew his stack.\n\u201cNow let\u2019s get this straight,\nhe told them when he\u2019d gather\ned the whole family in the liv\ning room. \u201cI know your inten\ntions are all right. I appreciate\nthat But there are some things\nyou may have forgotten.\n\u201cLook around this house. See\nthe furnishings? Recall for a\nminute that extra telephone up\nstairs especially for you kids.\nThink of the new car we bought\nlast month. Figure for a minute\nwhat it\u2019s going to cost to send\nyou kids to camp this summer.\n\u201cWHERE DO YOU suppose\nthese things come from? We\nhave them because I\u2019ve got a\ngood job at the plant. It\u2019s a\ngood job because we've got a\nunion and I get paid union\nwages. Do you suppose that the\npay increases I\u2019ve received came\nout of the goodness of the boss\nheart? Remember a couple of\nyears ago when we had to strike\nfor three weeks to get a fair\nincrease and a pension plan.\n\u201cNow suppose that people had\ncrossed our picket line that time;\nWhere would we be now? 1\nthe company had persuaded en\nough people to cross that line,\nthey\u2019d have broken the strike.\nMaybe we wouldn\u2019t have a un\nion now. Maybe I wouldn\u2019t get\na two-week vacation with pay\nthis summer.\n\u201cI don\u2019t care how long a\nstrike goes on. There\u2019s one rule\nthis family can never break. We\ndon\u2019t cross a picket line for\nanything. When you cross a\npicket line you\u2019re clobbering\nsomebody like us. You\u2019re break-!\ning faith, not only with pickets,\nbut with yourself.\u201d\nDad didn\u2019t make speeches of\nten to the whole family and this\none was delivered in tones\nwhich made the family know\nhe meant what he said.\nLater, the kids, after buying\ndad an atrocious necktie add a\nloud pair of socks he\u2019d never\n'have nerve enough to wear,'\nJunior told Sis: I\n'Dad certainly is the great-;\nest he\u2019s the greatest because\n,s _ a Knbot line.\nhe\u2019d never cross a picket line.;\nAnd when you think it over, i\nhow can anybody?\u201d I\nhow can anybody?\u201d\nI\nNo Waiting\u2014Just Leave \u2019Em i\n9X12 SHAG RUGS\nWASHED DRIED\n$3.75\nwith this ad\nunder 30 lbs.\nWE ALSO DYE and\nSKID-PROOF RUGS\nFriendly Laundromat\n3644 Upton GR 4-6096\nYour Duds Are Washed in\nSeparate Tubs\"\nI\nDumplings Tasty\nWith Chicken Stew\nThere are many quick and\nnasy dinners available, already\npackaged and ready to eat when\nheated, but it\u2019s nice to start with\nJust the foods themselves and\ncook them yourself.\nOne of the most savory of\nthese s Chicken Paprika,\nbrowned and then simmered un-|\ntil the chicken is tender. Add a\nspecial touch with mushroom\nsoup folded into the dumplings\nwhich are not much more than\na biscuit batter, easily mixed.\nChicken Paprika\n(Serves 6\n13% -pound roasting chicken\n1 cup flour\n1 tablespoon paprika\n1 tablespoon salt\n1 tablespoon monosodium\nglutamate\ncup shortening\n2 cups water\nCut chicken in serving size\npieces Dredge with flour mixed\nwith paprika, salt and monoso\ndium glutamate. Heat shortening,\nin skillet. Add chicken and\nbrown on all sides. Place chick-,\nen in heavy pan and add water.\nCover and cook until tender on\nlow heat, about 1 to 1% hours.'\nDrop mushroom dumplings from\ntablespoon right on to chicken.\nCook for 15 minutes without re\nmoving cover.\nMushroom Dumplings\n(Makes 10 to 12 dumplings)\n1 cup sifted all-purpose flour\n2 teaspoons baking powder\n33 teaspoon salt\n3 tablespoons cold water\n2 tablespoons parsley flakes\n12 cup condensed cream of\nmushroom soup\nSift together flour, baking\npowder and salt. Add water,\nparsley flakes, and soup (undi\n11 u ted to ingredients. Mix\ni enough to dampen flour. Drop\nby tablespoons onto chicken\npieces and cook as directed\nI above.\nKitchen Sanitation\nVital to Health\nHave you been brain-washed\nof hand washing by the wonder\ndrugs? Medical authorities have\n(been reminding surgeons to re\nturn to thorough hand scrubbing\nbefore operations. Could it be\nthat homemakers need some of\nthe same advice?\nKitchen sanitation cannot be\noveremphasized. Modern design\nand work-saving appliances\nhave a real and permanent place\n\u25a0in our current scheme of things.\nbut cleanliness is still the first\nmeasure of a good kitchen.\n1 With fancy hood over the\nrange to rid the kitchen of odors\nand blow out much of the\nsmoke, it's true kitchens don\u2019t\n'get as dirty, but they do need\ncleaning. You may have an au\ntomatic dishwasher, but what\nabout all those other small\nbatches of dishes which don\u2019t\nget automatically washed?\nGet Rid of Germs\nGerms thrive where there is\nmoisture and food scraps or\ntraces of food. That\u2019s one of the\nreasons dish towels are simply\nnot good health procedure. It\u2019s\nmuch healthier, in the absence\nof a dishwasher, to pour boiling\nwater over the dishes and allow\nthem to dry in a rack.\nDinnerware which chips and\ncracks easily should be replaced,\nas germs can lodge in the dishes\nwhich are not completely whole.\nUse a scrubbing brush on silver\nware to clean it thoroughly after\na good soaking. Shiny pots and\npans discourage germs, too.\nTidy Kitchens\nKitchens themselves should be\nkept immaculate. If yours is\nmodern, then there probably are\nmany aids to this, such as a\nplace for everything and every\nthing in its place. When coun\nters are kept clear of containers\nand appliances, they are easy to\nclean with soap and water. It\u2019s\nmuch more work to clear, then\nclean them if they\u2019re cluttered.\nQuality Meats\nFree Delivery Service\nGRAMLING\nBROS.\nMEAT MARKET\n502 Tecumseh Street\nCorner of Collingwood\nJoseph\u2014CH 1-8269\u2014Andrew\nS S. CANADIANA\nSAILS DAILY\nfrom the\nfoot of\nMADISON\nAVENUE\nBOB-LO\nCRUISE\u2014Everyday\nLV 9:30 A M\nMT. 6:30 P.M.\nAdults $2.50\nChildren *130\nUnder 13\nSUNSET CRUISE Tues., Wed,\nThurs., and Sun.\nLV. 8:00 P.M.\nAdults *1 SO\nRET. 11:00 P.M. Children *1.00\nMOONLITE CRUISE\u2014\nFri. Sat\nLV 800 P.M.\nRET. 13:00\nAdults $2.00\nChildren *1.00\nMonday Nites Open for\nPrivate Charter\nChildren Under 6 Free\nFor Special Group Reduced\nRate*\nCall CH 3-61 11\nSEAWAY EXCURSION\nLINES\nSHORT SToRy\nSHORT\nRemember\n56 A.D.\nBy Helen R. Moffitt\nKATHY first noticed It on her\nhoneymoon. When Jim took\noff his wristwatch, on the back\nof it, inscribed in neat, small\nletters were a number, and then\nthe letters \u201d58 A.D.\nI\nShe tried to ask him what it\nmeant but somehow the words\nwouldn't come. And although it\nbothered her\ncontinually\nI\nshe\nd i d n\u2019t\nhave the cour\n3\nage to ask\n-Minato\nPast..\nrwuM\n9 P 0\nJim, \u2018What does the inscription\nmean?\u201d\nI\n56 was a date, of course...\n\"But\u2014A.D. who was A.D.\u2019\u201d\nThe little town of Janesville,\nwhere Jim brought his bride to\nlive, was pleasant.1 The people\nat the country club gatherings\nwere all old school friends of\nJim\u2019s, and they'd been nice to\nher. Still Kathy eyed the women\nwarily and asked what their\nfirst names were, almost as soon\nas she\u2019d met them.\nWhen Kathy put on her new\nI\nturquoise and gold dress for the'\nSaturday night dance at the:\nclub, she was pleased with the)\ns\" ii \u00ab'r ii i ii nn.v^w\nh\n\u201cWhat\u2019s the matter, Kathy?\u201d\nasked Dick when he noticed\nher white face.\nway the colors brought out the\nblue of her eyes and the high\nlights in her brown hair. At the\nsame time, she wondered what\ncolor hair and eyes A.D. had.\nJim and Kathy had just en\ntered the club lounge when\nCandie Bruce came at them\nwith, \u201cI've a surprise for you.\n{Jim.\u201d And she pushed forward\n4.11 11 41 e\na tall blonde with soft brown\neyes. \u201cYou remember Abbie?\u201d\nJim gave every indication he I\nknew her, even to including a\nkiss. While Kathy stood silently\nby, a cold hand clutched her\nheart. Jim said, Abbie, this is\nKathy, my wife Kathy, this\nis Abbie Dickson.\u201d\nAbbie Dickson... A.D. Kathy\nknew then.\nIt was at a dance at the club\ntwo weeks after Abbie\u2019s arrival\nthat it happened. Jim was danc\ning with Abbie. When Kathy\nand Dick Crane danced near\nthem on the crowded floor. Just\na few words of conversation, but\nlit was enough. \u201cWhen?\u201d asked\nI Jim. \u201cTen o\u2019clock in the morn\ning, at the airport,\u201d answered\nAbbie as they danced away.\nKathy felt her heart grow\ncold. Jim was going with Ab\nbie on the plane somewhere. He\nloved her.\n\u201cWhat\u2019s the matter, Kathy?\u201d\nasked Dick when he noticed her\nwhite face.\n\u201cIt's a headache, Dick. Please\ntake me home.\u201d\nWhen they reached her house\nKathy asked Dick to tell Jim\nnot to disturb her when he re\nturned.\nShe locked herself into a\nspare bedroom where she sat\nalone in the darkness. When fi\nnally she went to bed and to\nsleep, it was nine-thirty the next\nmorning when she awoke. Nine\nthirty, and the plane left at ten.\nShe had to see Jim again, she\nwouldn\u2019t talk to him but just\nlook at him once more. She lit\nerally threw her clothes on.\n(When she reached the airport\nshe was too late, the plane was\n{gone. She stood in the large\nI waiting room, white-faced and\ndazed. Suddenly someone called\nher name.\n\"Kathy, what are you doing\nhere?\u201d\nCandie never gave anyone a\nchance to answer. As usual, she\nran on. \u201cI\u2019ve just seen Abblie\noff. She\u2019s so happy. Pat\u2019s coming\nhome. She\u2019s flying to the coast\nto meet him.\u201d\n\u201cP\u2014Pat?\u201d\n\u201cYes, of course her hus\nband. She was just married a\nweek when he was sent to\nKorea.\u201d\nKathy felt as if a heavy weight\nhad been lifted from her shoul\nders as she smiled at Candie.\nThat evening Kathy said to\nJim, \u201cWhat\u2019s the inscription on\nyour wrist watch?\u201d\nJim grinned. \u201cDidn\u2019t I tell\nyou. I had it done right after I\njoined the air force 56th\nAirborne Division.\u201d\nJim stared at Kathy's beam\ning face. \u201cYou\u2019re beautiful, hon\ney, just beautiful,\u201d he said softly.\nRent eur Bug Cleaning Machine\nand elean your own wall to wall\nearpets or\nBring this\nrugs to your own home\nad and save $2 on our\nregular S* rental charge (24 hours)\nPIZZA CLEANERS\n1013 Starr Ave. OX 1-3062\nLet\u2019s Go Shopping\nI\nStrawberries Make Meals\nStand Out; Good Anytime\nThere\u2019s something about strawberries that make even the\nmere thought of them delightful. Most persons would agree any\nway that strawberries lend an air of distinction to a meal. This\nversatile fruit may be served \u2019round the clock as a breakfast\nfruit, in salads, desserts, appetizers, or a between-meals treat.\nWith fresh berries of good\nquality on the market right now\nyou may want to enjoy this fruit\noften.\nFor tops in\nstrawberry\nquality and\nflavor, market\ning specialists\nadvise select\ning berries\nthat are a uni\nform bright\ncolor, clean\nand fresh, dry\nyet glossy in\nappear ance.\nl\ni\n\nMrs. Spear\nand still have the green cap.\ni\nFresh berries are highly per\nishable. Buy only as many as can\ncan be used in a day or two. Re\nmove soft or spoiled berries as\nsoon as you reach home and\nstore the remainder in the re\nfrigerator.\nDO NOT WASH until just be\n.fore you are ready to prepare\nfor serving. Just before Using,'\nwash gently and quickly in a\nbowl of cold water. After ber-i\nties are clean and fully dry, re\nmove the green caps.\nIn shopping. when comparing\nj the cost of fresh and frozen ber\nries, the cost per serving is the\nthe same when a 10-ounce frozen\npackage sells at half the price\nof a quart of fresh berries. For\nfreezing berries look for the va\nriety \u201cSparkle\u201d. It is excellent\nfor this purpose. i\nMarilynettes Notes\nThe Local 12 Marilynettes\nMarching Unit participated in\nthe Peony Festival in Van Wert,\nOhio, Wednesday.\nThe Junior Marilynettes are\nappearing in competition in Wa\npakoneta, Saturday.\nThe Marilynettes wish to\nthank everyone who attended\nthe Chicken Bar-B-Q last Sun\nday and helped to make it a suc\ncess.\nWhat has not unselfed love\nachieved for the race?\n\u2014Mary Baker Eddy\nPHILLIPS INN\nA Union Bar Restaurant\nItaian Spaghetti\u2014Chili\nChops, Steaks, Chicken, Fish\n384 Phillips OR 2-0354\nt\npeMop\"\n[rove\nThe\n60\"sore\nn\u2019S\nl\n112,19101\nCH. v\nBRIDES LOVE FLOWERS\n2\n2\nhom*i r\n9*Wg***e\nhoott\nARLINGTON FLOWER SHOP\nSay It With Flowere In Any Event\n2110 ARLINGTON\nW Albridge 9531\nBAYVIEW GREENHOUSE\nFlowere Direct From Our Own Greenhouee To You\nRA. 6-6189 3650 SUPER AVE. Open Sunday \u2019Til Nona\nESTELLE FLOWER SHOP\nA Complete Satiefying Service\n737 WEST CENTRAL\nCH. 4-3074\n0\nEDINGTON FLOWERS GREENHOUSE\nFlowere and Plante Dieh Gardene Our Specialty\n5525 EPGEWATER PR.\nRA. 6-3845\nFLORA'S FLOWER SHOP\nCereagee Wedding Flowere\nPlante\n5348 MONROE ST.\nPottery and Gifts\nFloral Deeigne\nLU. 2-3980\nMacCARTNEY\nBROS.\n\u201cWe Deliver the Goodt\u201d\n408 JUNCTION Sine\u00bb 1926\nAlwayi Fruh\nCH 8-5568\n\nLOU PEATEE\nFlowert and Gifit for AU Occationt\n2434 SYLVANIA AVE.\nGR. 5-1539\n\nHELMER FLOWER SHOP\nYour compleit taiitfaciion it our guarantor\n2237 ASHLAND AVE.\nCH. 3-5324\nSUDER THE FLORIST\nSinca 1870\n3003 CHERRY ST.\nCH. 4-9551\n1315 CHERRY\nSa...\u201cla 9\nCH. 8-5361\nSWIETZER\u2019S FLOWER SHOP\nFloral Dotigning\u2014Plania\u2014Cuf Flowart\n3037 TREMAINSVILLE\nGR. 4-7123\nTIMM'S FLOWER SHOP\nFor Perfect Exprettion of Sentiment\nSend Froth Flowert From Our Groenhoute\n2801 DORR STREET\nFRanklin 1441\n\nHARRY TURVEY FLORIST\nFreth Flowert From Our Own Greenhoute\n360 PHILLIPS AVE.\nGR. 2-2028\n\nMARY A. WARNING Flowers\nWm. J. Smith Mgr.\n1217 BROADWAY\nCH. 1-6231\n\nPAUL ANSTED\u2019S FLORISTS\nMatiert in The Art of Floral Detign\n4436 MONROE\nGR 2-2749 GR 9-4550","height":"26776","width":"19396"}}
